# CostGuard — .cursorrules

## Project
CostGuard: Real-time AI/cloud spend monitoring SaaS with automated kill switches.
Stack: Next.js 14 (App Router) + TypeScript + Supabase + Prisma + Upstash Redis/QStash + Stripe.

## Hard Rules

### Security — NEVER violate
- NEVER log, return, or expose `encryptedCreds` or decrypted credentials in API responses
- ALWAYS verify Supabase session before any DB operation in API routes
- ALWAYS validate that platform.userId === authenticated user.id before any mutation
- NEVER store plaintext API keys anywhere — always use `encrypt()` from `src/lib/crypto.ts`
- QStash webhook MUST verify signature using `@upstash/qstash` Receiver before processing

### Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any` except in adapter rawResponse fields
- All async functions must have try/catch or use `withRetry()`
- No default exports except Next.js pages and layout files
- Zod validation on ALL API route inputs
- Prisma transactions for any multi-table write

### Architecture
- Business logic lives ONLY in `src/modules/` — never in API routes or components
- API routes are thin: auth check → call module function → return response
- Each adapter implements `PlatformAdapter` interface from `base.adapter.ts`
- Adding a new platform = create one adapter file + register in `adapter-factory.ts` — nothing else changes
- Redis is for speed (latest readings, locks, windows) — Postgres is source of truth

### UI
- All colors via CSS variables (`--kill`, `--safe`, `--warn`, `--cyan`, `--text`, `--muted`)
- Status colors: CLOSED=safe green, OPEN=kill red, HALF_OPEN=warn yellow
- Distance-to-threshold gauge is THE hero component — always visible on dashboard
- No toast for successful background operations — only for user-triggered actions
- Loading states on ALL async operations

### Testing
- Every algorithm in `src/modules/circuit-breaker/` must have a Vitest unit test
- Kill switch flow must have a Playwright E2E test
- Run `npm test` before any commit

## File Headers
Every new file starts with:
```typescript
// src/modules/[module]/[file].ts
// CostGuard — [one-line description]
```

## Commit Convention
feat: implement OpenAI adapter
fix: circuit breaker half-open window
test: burn rate sliding window edge cases
refactor: extract alert dispatcher
